channel.title: [Pi] Small error [Pi]
channel.description:
Hey guys, so I was trying to fix up my FightCaves (with the help of some tutorials) and after I thought I was done, I compiled, and got this error.
[code]src\server\model\players\Client.java:1013: cannot find symbol symbol : variable fightCaves location: class server.Server Server.fightCaves.spawnNextWave((Client) PlayerHandler.players[playerId]); ^ src\server\model\players\PlayerAssistant.java:2370: cannot find symbol symbol : variable fightCaves location: class server.Server Server.fightCaves.spawnNextWave((Client)PlayerHa ndler.players[c.playerId]); ^ src\server\model\npcs\NPCHandler.java:1245: cannot find symbol symbol : variable fightCaves location: class server.Server Server.fightCaves.spawnNextWave( c2); ^ Note: Some input files use unchecked or unsafe operations. Note: Recompile with -Xlint:unchecked for details. 3 errors Press any key to continue . . .[/code]
I don't quite understand why it's telling me it can't find server.Server, for things such as my fightPits, I have it in the same form, and that works just fine. I know spawnNextWave is in my FightCaves.java, and I've imported fightcaves and server, does anybody know the problem?
